body_content.explanation: a national park (= a large area of land protected by the government because of its natural beauty or because it has a special history) in the US state of Utah:
examples: Arches National Park preserves over 2,000 natural sandstone arches and other unusual rock formations, creating a landscape of contrasting colors, landforms, and textures.
Arches National Park has just one entrance, located east of US-191 five miles north of Moab.
